# Vite writes into this directory (see web/vite.config.ts). The build
# artifacts are not committed — Vite regenerates them per build with
# content-hashed filenames. We DO commit two files so //go:embed all:dist
# compiles in a fresh checkout and the Handler has a useful fallback:
#   - this .gitignore
#   - index.stub.html (served when no real index.html is present)
#
# `npm --prefix web run build` runs scripts/clean-dist.mjs before Vite,
# which clears everything here EXCEPT the two files above — so real builds
# never dirty the working tree.
*
!.gitignore
!index.stub.html
